  HOW TO CREATE FORM IN HTML?
<form action="/submit" method="POST">

<form> </form>:- The tag used defined the form contianer.
action= This attribute specifies the URL that will process the form data  after submission
Method:= http method(GET OR POST) used  after submitting the form data.

 <input type="text" id="name" name="name"><br><br>
<input>:- The tag used to create different type if input elements such as text fileds  checkboxes and radio buttons

type:-=  checkboxes and radio buttons and text, and submit
name := this attribue assigns a name to the input element which is used to identify the form data when submitted

<label> to provide a text albel for input elements , improving the accessibility and usability of the form.

<textarea>:= Mutlti-field input field.

<select> or <option> these tags are used to create a drop-down list of options for the user to choose form.





